{
  "abstract": "The ‘New Deal’ to rural India is aligned with a ‘pro-poor\r\npeople centred ‘ perspective for development. It underlines\r\ngrowth based on efficiency and equity and stimulates the\r\nagricultural economy to boost incomes, demand and growth\r\nacross the vast rural heartland, home to 72% of India’s\r\npopulation.",
